cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.RO 

This paper is about training deep models for lane detection, which is a computer vision task. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also introduces a novel knowledge distillation approach, which involves training a model to learn from itself, and this falls under the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also uses convolutional neural networks (CNNs), which is a subfield of deep learning and falls under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper is related to robotics, as lane detection is an important task for autonomous vehicles, and this falls under cs.RO (Robotics).
